core:processNote.core:description: StartPedUpdateTms event is raised from user process CardPayment/UpdateICCReaderSoftwareTms to start or attempt to start an update manually. TMSClient raises some events as updates start. Status event is used to indicate checking for an update. If no update is received, updateStatusPrompt will eventually time out and return to not visible prompt PedEventWait state.

core:state.core:comment: An extra state to try to ensure that SoftwareUpdatePrompt ManualUpdateCheck, etc get closed before returning to PEDEventWait
